claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: The image shows the table of contents and editorial credits from an MMWR publication. It lists sections such as Introduction, Methods, Primary Changes and Updates, Recommendations for the Use of Influenza Vaccines, etc., along with CDC editorial and production staff names. The image does not support the claim because it contains only the publication's contents and staff listings; there is no mention of Flublok, Fluarix, or any pivotal trial comparing the two vaccines. This content does not support the claim. Note: Analysis limited to the visible page, which appears to be front-matter without study details.
